CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 9, reads: "Where Mother Threw Baby - Mrs. Ross Nicotera threw her baby to Amos Fred from the window marked with an 'X,' to save it from fire which destroyed this three-story building, on Monday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire damaged three story brick building with second story porch, man in doorway, and police sawhorse on sidewalk, Pennsylvania Avenue at Fulton Street, Northside
